title: Minneapolis and the Age of Railways (History US Ebook).pdf
description:
Minneapolis and the Age of Railways
University of Minnesota Press | 2005 | English | ISBN: 0816645019 | 352 pages | PDF | 53 MB

Hofsommer (history, St. Cloud State U.) presents a history of the relationship between Minneapolis and its railroads from about 1865 to 1920. He considers the part played by industries, construction of the railroads and lines, owners and rail companies, financial difficulties, and their rise and decline in popularity.
